\f1\b \cf0 Prerequisite:
\f0\b0  This lab assumes you have already deployed the ambient expense agent to Agent Runtime. If you have not completed this step, please finish the prerequisite codelab first: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/enterprise-cloud-scale-deploying-the-expense-agent-to-agent-runtime-on-google-cloud"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Deploy an ADK agent to Agent Runtime using Agents CLI}}.\
In the previous lab, you 
\f1\b vibecoded
\f0\b0  an ambient expense agent and 
\f1\b deployed it to Agent Runtime on Google Cloud
\f0\b0 . While your agent is now live in the cloud, interacting with it requires making direct API requests or issuing prompts from the Google Cloud Console.\
In this codelab, you will give your agent a 
\f1\b fully functional front door and a human-in-the-loop management dashboard
\f0\b0 . Acting as the 
\f1\b software architect
\f0\b0 , you will guide 
\f1\b Antigravity
\f0\b0  (Google's agentic IDE) to vibecode a web-based 
\f1\b Manager Dashboard
\f0\b0 , deploy it to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.google.com/run"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Cloud Run}}, and integrate it with an 
\f1\b asynchronous, event-driven architecture
\f0\b0  powered by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.google.com/pubsub"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Pub/Sub}}.\
