\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 3. Vibecode a frontend dashboard for the Expense Agent}}
\f1\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 With your cloud environment configured and agent verified, you now need a mechanism for managers to interact with paused agent sessions and approve expenses. When an expense report exceeds the $100 threshold, the ambient expense agent automatically halts execution at a human-in-the-loop 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 RequestInput
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  node and preserves its state within the Agent Platform Session Service.\
To make these paused sessions actionable, you will guide Antigravity to vibe-code a standalone FastAPI web application. FastAPI is a popular web framework for building APIs with Python. This service acts as the bridge: it dynamically queries the session service for pending approvals, presents them in an elegant interactive web UI, and provides endpoints to securely resume the agent's execution on Agent Runtime once a decision is made.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic frontend_1920.png \width38400 \height19800 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 \
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  
\f1\b Prompt to Antigravity:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 Vibe-code a standalone manager-dashboard service in a new folder\
"submission_frontend/". I want:\
\
\'a0 - A FastAPI service with the following endpoints:\
\'a0 \'a0 1. GET /: Serves a beautiful, interactive manager dashboard HTML page. Use Outfit or Inter Google Fonts, sleek glassmorphism styling (dark background, radial glows, cards with backdrop blurs and subtle borders). It should fetch pending approvals from the backend and display them as interactive cards.\
\'a0 \'a0 2. GET /api/pending: Queries the ADK VertexAiSessionService to list all sessions, fetches the full history for each session, and identifies unresolved `adk_request_input` function call events (events requesting input that do not have a corresponding `adk_request_input` function response event). Returns the session ID, interrupt ID, and expense payload details.\
\'a0 \'a0 3. POST /api/action/\{session_id\}: Resumes the paused session on Agent Runtime. To avoid duplicate parameter errors on the ADK runner, pass the resume payload (with role: user and parts: [function_response: \{id: interrupt_id, name: adk_request_input, response: \{approved: True/False\}\}]) directly as the dict value of the `message` argument to the SDK. Also make sure to set the `user_id` strictly to "default-user" to avoid session ownership mismatch errors.\
\'a0 - Read the GCP project and AGENT_RUNTIME_ID from environment variables.\
\
\'a0 - A pyproject.toml with fastapi, uvicorn, google-adk, and google-cloud-aiplatform.\
\
Make sure the UI looks highly polished and premium (colors, transitions, interactive approve/reject actions with loading spinners, and a modal that slides out to display the agent's final compliance review). Show me the main.py implementation when done.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 What to expect:
\f0\b0  Antigravity will scaffold a new directory named 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 submission_frontend/
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  containing a 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 pyproject.toml
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  for dependency management and a fully implemented 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 main.py
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  FastAPI service. It will construct the three requested endpoints (
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 GET /
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 , 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 GET /api/pending
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 , and 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 POST /api/action/\{session_id\}
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 ) and generate the HTML/CSS frontend with premium glassmorphic styling. Once complete, Antigravity will present the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 main.py
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  code for your review.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/vibecode-frontend-with-antigravity#3"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 4. Deploy the Dashboard to Cloud Run}}
\f1\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 With the FastAPI web application fully scaffolded in your local 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 submission_frontend
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  directory, the next step is to deploy it to a secure, scalable, serverless environment. By deploying to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.google.com/run"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Cloud Run}}, Google Cloud's fully managed container platform, your dashboard receives a public HTTPS endpoint accessible anywhere.\
Furthermore, the dashboard acts as the operational bridge, querying the Agent Platform Session Service for paused sessions and invoking the agent to resume execution. Therefore, its runtime service account must be granted explicit Identity and Access Management (IAM) permissions (
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 roles/aiplatform.user
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 ) to securely interact with these cloud resources.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  
\f1\b Prompt to Antigravity:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 Deploy the submission_frontend folder as "expense-manager-dashboard" to Cloud Run. Pass\
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT, and AGENT_RUNTIME_ID as environment variables, and configure the deployment to allow unauthenticated invocations so it is publicly reachable. After it deploys, grant the dashboard's runtime service account the necessary roles on the project so it can resume the Agent\
Runtime agent and query its sessions. Print the Dashboard URL when done.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 What to expect:
\f0\b0  Antigravity will package your FastAPI application and perform a source-based deployment to Cloud Run. Once the service is live, it will retrieve the auto-generated runtime service account and assign it the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 roles/aiplatform.user
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  IAM role on your project. Finally, Antigravity will verify the deployment and output the live HTTPS URL for your Manager Dashboard.\

\f1\b (Note: This deployment takes several minutes.)
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/vibecode-frontend-with-antigravity#4"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 5. Build the Pub/Sub topic}}
\f1\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 In this step, you will establish the foundational messaging backbone for your event-driven architecture. You will create a primary {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cloud.google.com/pubsub/docs/overview"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 Pub/Sub}} topic to receive incoming expense events and a companion 
\f1\b dead-letter topic (DLT)
\f0\b0  to capture any undeliverable messages. This decouples the ingestion of expense reports from the downstream execution of the agent, ensuring robust, asynchronous processing at scale.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  
\f1\b Prompt to Antigravity:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 Create the Pub/Sub topics for my event pipeline. I want:\
\'a0 1. A Pub/Sub topic called "expense-reports" for incoming expense events.\
\'a0 2. A dead-letter topic called "expense-reports-dead-letter" so messages that fail repeatedly don't get lost.\
\
Use gcloud commands. Walk me through each one before you run it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 What to expect:
\f0\b0  Antigravity will explain its plan and execute the necessary 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 gcloud pubsub topics create
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  commands. It will verify that both the primary 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 expense-reports
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  topic and the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 expense-reports-dead-letter
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  topic are successfully provisioned in your Google Cloud project.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/vibecode-frontend-with-antigravity#5"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 6. Wire Pub/Sub to Agent Runtime}}
\f1\b\fs36 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 To complete your event-driven architecture, you need to connect your Pub/Sub ingestion topic to the deployed AI agent. In traditional architectures, developers often build and maintain an intermediary microservice (such as a Cloud Function) solely to pull messages from Pub/Sub and forward them to an AI model's API.\
However, Google Cloud Pub/Sub provides advanced push capabilities that eliminate the need for this intermediary compute layer. By creating an {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://openid.net/developers/how-connect-works/"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 OpenID Connect}} (OIDC)-authenticated 
\f1\b push subscription
\f0\b0  targeting the Agent Runtime's REST API, Pub/Sub can invoke your agent directly. Crucially, configuring this subscription with the 
\f1\b NoWrapper
\f0\b0  (
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 --push-no-wrapper
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 ) feature instructs Pub/Sub to strip away the outer Pub/Sub event envelope, delivering the raw JSON expense payload exactly as expected by the agent's input schema. To guarantee enterprise reliability, you will also configure an acknowledgment deadline (accommodating complex LLM reasoning passes) and automated routing to your dead-letter topic after 5 failed attempts.\
\uc0\u55357 \u56393  
\f1\b Prompt to Antigravity:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs26 \cf0 \strokec2 Create the authenticated Pub/Sub push subscription pointing directly to Agent Runtime. I want:\
\'a0 1. A service account called "pubsub-invoker" for Pub/Sub push authentication.\
\'a0 2. Permission granted to that service account to query and invoke my Agent Runtime agent.\
\'a0 3. The OIDC-authenticated push subscription "expense-reports-push" delivering directly to the Agent Runtime's :query REST API, using `--push-no-wrapper` to unwrap the payload, and configured with a 10-minute ack deadline and a dead-letter topic after 5 failed attempts.\
\
Use gcloud commands. Walk me through each one before running.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 What to expect:
\f0\b0  Antigravity will provision a dedicated service account (
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 pubsub-invoker
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 ) and assign it the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 roles/aiplatform.user
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  role to invoke the agent. It will grant the Pub/Sub service agent permission to mint OIDC tokens (
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator
\f0\fs24 \strokec2 ). Antigravity will then extract your Agent Runtime ID from 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 deployment_metadata.json
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  and create the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 expense-reports-push
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  subscription targeting the 
\f3\fs26 \strokec2 :query
\f0\fs24 \strokec2  endpoint with the unwrapped payload and Dead-Letter Topic policy configured.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
