\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Architectural Data Flow\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Asynchronous Ingestion:
\f0\b0  When an expense report is published to the 
\f3\fs26 expense-reports
\f0\fs24  Pub/Sub topic, it is decoupled from the caller. A push subscription instantly forwards the raw payload to the deployed Agent Runtime (
\f3\fs26 :query
\f0\fs24  REST API).\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Automated Branching:
\f0\b0  The AI agent evaluates the expense amount. Low-value requests (< $100) complete instantly. High-value requests (>= $100) pause execution at a human-in-the-loop 
\f3\fs26 RequestInput
\f0\fs24  node and persist their session state in the Agent Platform Session Service.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Management Loop:
\f0\b0  The standalone Cloud Run dashboard dynamically polls the Session Service for active paused sessions, presents them on an elegant web UI, and issues secure IAM-authenticated calls back to Agent Runtime to resume execution once a manager clicks Approve or Reject.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://codelabs.developers.google.com/vibecode-frontend-with-antigravity#7"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\b\fs36 \cf3 \ul \ulc3 \strokec3 8. Run it end to end}}
